news.title: 'Smart upgrade' for streetlights on nine roads in new sectors of Gurugram
news.para: The first-of-its-kind initiative will be rolled out on roads between Sectors 76 and 77, 75A and 76, 75 and 75A, 73 and 74, 71 and 73, 70 and 75, 70 and 70A, 68 and 69, and 68 and 70, which house several schools, gated societies, offices and commercial spaces and see a high volume of vehicular and pedestrian movement.

news.title: China: New home price growth stalls in February as demand remains frail
news.para: Average new home prices in China's 70 major cities were flat at 0.00% month-on-month, compared with a 0.1% gain in January, according to Reuters calculations based on data released by the National Bureau of Statistics (NBS).

news.title: Indore: Complaints against cooperative societies during public hearing
news.para: Among the complainants were a group of around 100 people, who alleged colonisers of Akshardham Colony situated in Musakhedi area. ADM Pavan Jain assured the complainants to launch a probe into the matter.

news.title: Noida: How much explosives needed to raze Supertech twin towers, asks CBRI
news.para: The Central Building Research Institute (CBRI) has sought to know from the private company assigned the task of demolishing the twin towers the amount of explosives that would be needed to bring them down.

news.title: Land registries done from 2010-2016 to be probed: Haryana CM
news.para: The chief minister said this during the discussion on opposition's calling attention motion regarding alleged irregularities in the registries done under the BJP-JJP government.

news.title: Piramal Capital ties up with IMGC to offer home loans of Rs 5-75 lakh
news.para: Piramal Capital & Housing Finance expects to generate around 10-12% of business from this partnership by the end of FY23.

news.title: Haryana: Soon, deeds for land within 100 meters of IAF station
news.para: ​Haryana deputy chief minister Dushyant Chautala gave this assurance in response to a question raised by Faridabad NIT MLA Neeraj Sharma during the budget session of Haryana legislative assembly on Tuesday.

news.title: Pay 50% security deposit before illegal construction hearing: Kolkata civic body
news.para: Following the newly framed rules as per the provision of the KMC Act, the person will need to deposit 50% of the calculated amount of fees and charges for retention of unauthorized construction prior to placing the matter before the special officer for hearing.

news.title: Madhya Pradesh: Over 5 lakh women to get new homes under PMAY-Rural on March 28
news.para: ​Prime Minister Narendra Modi will attend the programme virtually on the occasion, the official from the public relations department said quoting Chief Minister Shivraj Singh Chouhan.

news.title: Residents of private layouts in Mysuru left in the dark
news.para: In addition to the lack of streetlights plunging swathes of the area in darkness, the failure of the private owners, who have developed these layouts, to settle outstanding dues has resulted in the Chamundeshwari Electricity Supply Corporation (CESC) to disconnect power supply.

news.title: Ahmedabad civic body proposes to collect fire safety charges in advance
news.para: The civic body has proposed to collect fire safety charges — fire safety inspection and fire NOC renewal — once in three years for new buildings and once in two years for old highrises, instead of the current annual cycle.

news.title: Nod to 12-acre Thane cluster redevelopment plan
news.para: Thane municipal commissioner Dr Vipin Sharma, who made the announcement, said the Kisan Nagar cluster plan in Thane will be taken up in phases.

news.title: Work on town planning scheme for Mann-Mhalunge to begin by year-end
news.para: The state government had recently approved the changes made in the town planning scheme as 29 plots had to be re-allocated as they were in the flood line area. Seventeen plots in Mann and twelve in Mhalunge were in the flood line area as per the earlier proposal which was objected to.

news.title: Indore: 50 objections received over proposal to increase collector's guideline
news.para: The district-level evaluation committee of Indore stamp and registrar department had on March 10 proposed a 10% rise in collector’s guideline of properties in 431 localities and 25% increase in 144 areas of Indore district.

news.title: Credai Aurangabad says e-charging norms will raise house prices
news.para: Credai said the installation of average quality e-charging station for an apartment of 10 flat could cost minimum Rs 30,000 to Rs 50,000.
